  <description type="morphology">Stems 5–20 cm. Inflorescences 3–8-flowered. Flowers 1.2–1.8 mm, hairs of 2 sizes, long hairs 1/2–2/3 as long as sepals, short hairs 1/4–1/3 as long as sepals, tips of some or all hooked or tightly coiled; hypanthium area pubescent, tips of hairs hooked or tightly coiled; sepals in fruit ± unequal, of 2 lengths; stamens 2–3; styles distinct, 0.2–0.4 mm. Seeds 0.5–0.6 mm. 2n = 36 (Europe).</description>
